@startuml seq_20_private_messaging
title Sequence Diagram: UC-20 Private Messaging (E2EE)

actor User
participant "User Web (Client)" as Frontend
participant "Crypto Module" as Crypto
participant "Message Controller\n(WebSocket)" as Controller
participant "Message Service" as Service
participant "Message Repo" as Repo
participant "Event Bus\n(Go Channels)" as EventBus

User -> Frontend: (1.1) Open Messages
Frontend -> Controller: (1.2) GET /api/messages/channels
Controller -> Service: (2.1) Load user's channels and recent messages
Service -> Repo: (2.2) Find channels for user
Repo --> Service: (2.3) List of channels
Service --> Controller: (3.1) Channels data
Controller --> Frontend: (3.2) 200 OK (channels)
Frontend --> User: (3.3) Display conversation list

User -> Frontend: (4.1) Select a conversation
User -> Frontend: (5.1) Type a message and send it
Frontend -> Crypto: (5.2) Encrypt message with recipient's public key
Crypto --> Frontend: (5.3) Encrypted ciphertext
Frontend -> Controller: (5.4) WS Send {channel_id, ciphertext}
Controller -> Service: (6.1) Process message
Service -> Repo: (6.2) Validate channel membership and recipient settings
Repo --> Service: (6.3) Membership valid
Service -> Repo: (7.1) Persist encrypted message
Repo --> Service: (7.2) Message saved
Service -> EventBus: (8.1) Broadcast message to conversation members
EventBus --> Controller: (8.2) Push to recipient's WS connection
Controller -> Frontend: (8.3) WS deliver message (ciphertext)
Frontend -> Crypto: (8.4) Decrypt message
Crypto --> Frontend: (8.5) Plaintext message
Service -> Repo: (9.1) Mark channel as read for current user
Service --> Controller: (10.1) Delivery status
Frontend --> User: (10.2) Display new message
@enduml
